text.section:
A licensed optometrist may:
Use the title "optometrist";
If the optometrist holds the degree of doctor of optics or doctor of optometry from a college or university authorized to give the degree, use the title "Doctor" or the abbreviations "Dr." or "O.D." with the optometrist's name;
If the optometrist is certified under § 11-404 of this subtitle, use the title "diagnostically certified optometrist"; and
If the optometrist is certified under § 11-404.1 of this subtitle, use the title "therapeutically certified optometrist".
